#!/usr/bin/env perl
use v5.40;
use FindBin;
use lib "$FindBin::Bin/../lib";
use Typist::Check;
Typist::Check->run(@ARGV);

__END__

=head1 NAME

typist-check - Static type checker for Perl files using Typist

=head1 SYNOPSIS

    typist-check                         # Scan lib/ for .pm files
    typist-check lib/Shop/Order.pm       # Check specific file(s)
    typist-check --root src/             # Custom workspace root
    typist-check --no-color              # Disable colored output
    typist-check --verbose               # Show clean files too

=head1 DESCRIPTION

Runs Typist static analysis (type checking and effect checking) on Perl
source files and reports diagnostics to the terminal with colored output.
Uses the same cross-file workspace registry as the LSP server for
accurate cross-package resolution.

If no files are specified, scans C<lib/> (or the current directory if
C<lib/> does not exist) for C<.pm> files.

=head1 OPTIONS

=over 4

=item C<--root DIR>

Set the workspace root directory for cross-file type resolution.
Defaults to C<lib/> if it exists, otherwise the current directory.

=item C<--no-color>

Disable ANSI color codes in output. Also disabled automatically when
C<NO_COLOR> environment variable is set or stdout is not a terminal.

=item C<-v>, C<--verbose>

Show all checked files, including those with no diagnostics.

=item C<-h>, C<--help>

Print usage information and exit.

=back

=head1 EXIT CODES

=over 4

=item C<0> - All clean (no diagnostics)

=item C<1> - Errors found (severity 1-2: TypeMismatch, ArityMismatch, etc.)

=item C<2> - Warnings only (severity 3-4: UndeclaredTypeVar, UnknownType, etc.)

=back

=head1 ENVIRONMENT

=over 4

=item C<NO_COLOR>

When set, disables colored output (L<https://no-color.org>).

=back

=head1 SEE ALSO

L<Typist>, L<Typist::Check>, L<typist-lsp>

=cut
